{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the bursaries for teachers in all core STEM subjects to over \u00a320,000",
        "additional_details": "Recent cuts in Teacher Training Bursaries in Biology have decreased from \u00a326k to \u00a35k, leaving one to question: Which subject will the government cut next? With training fees often costing over \u00a39k a year, plus another \u00a310k needed for general maintenance (such as housing, transport, or food), the cuts in funding could result in a significant decrease in trainee teachers. This could worsen the Secondary School teacher shortage.",
        "background": "Increase all bursaries for trainee teachers in STEM above \u00a320,000 per academic year. There is already a massive shortage of teachers, especially in core subjects, and I feel the lack of funding will not be an incentive to train to teach.",
